<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-02T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-02T21:00:00-05:00" n="119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">747.47H/12: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Australia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canberra</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-03T13:00:00+11:00">February 3, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 3—5:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>25. Reference Department’s 10, February 1, 6 p.m. I presented text of
                                message to Prime Minister Curtin at noon today. Apparently Minister
                                External Affairs had not informed Prime Minister of my conversation
                                with him on January 21 communicating our ideas.</p>
                            <p>Curtin authorized me to assure you that there is no immediacy
                                involved in plan for calling conference and stated that he would
                                give me a considered reply shortly.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>